Lewiston State Bank RIBII.1. for December 2014 = 880,000		As of September 29, 2015, Lewiston State Bank and Bank of American Fork, wholly-owned subsidiaries of People's Utah Bancorp (PUB), were combined into People's Intermountain Bank (the bank charter of Bank of American Fork renamed People's Intermountain Bank). Following the guidance of Accounting Standards Codification (ASC) 805-50, since the two banks are controlled by PUB, on this Call Report the business combination has been accounted for as a merger of entities under common control and the carrying amount of the assets, liabilities and net assets have been combined as if a pooling-of-interests. All beginning balances were restated as if the bank combination occurred as of the beginning of the year.
